  "text": "Here we demonstrated that females show greater generalization of context fear conditioning than males as well as sexspecific patterns of retrieval-induced cFos in hippocampus and amygdala. Together with previous findings demonstrating that hippocampal activation correlates with less generalization of context fear in males [CITATION_1] because of its role in retrieval of detailed information about context [CITATION_2] , our results suggest that males and females utilize different neural correlates or molecular mechanisms in retrieval of context-associated memories.",
